Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reset_property(25.10)                                    reset_property(25.10)

Name
       reset_property

Syntax
       reset_property

       [-object_type {<object_type>}]

       {<object_list>}

       <property_name>

       Resets  user-defined  properties  on objects set using the set_property
       command.

Parameters
       <object_list>
              Specifies a list of objects for which the property is to be  re-
              set.

       -object_type {<object_type>}
              Specifies  the type of object on which the property is to be re-
              set.

       <property_name>
              Specifies the name of the property for  which  the  user-defined
              property is to be reset.

Examples
              * The  following  command  resets user-defined property slk from
                pins C1/A:

                reset_property [get_pins C1/A] slk

Related Information
              * get_property

              * report_property

              * define_property

              * set_property

